  "local_port": 48148,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some smart questions to ask a CEO over a lunch meeting?",
  "response": "It's important to prepare thoughtful questions that can lead to insightful conversations and demonstrate your genuine interest in the company and its leadership. Here are some smart questions you might consider asking a CEO over a lunch meeting:\n\n1. **Vision and Strategy**\n   - How do you see the company's vision evolving over the next five to ten years?\n   - What are the key strategic priorities for the company right now?\n\n2. **Leadership and Management**\n   - How would you describe your leadership style, and how do you think it influences the company culture?\n   - What qualities do you value most in your leadership team?\n\n3. **Industry Outlook**\n   - What are the biggest challenges and opportunities you see in our industry?\n   - How do you stay informed about emerging trends and technologies in the sector?\n\n4. **Company Insights**\n   - What differentiates our company from its competitors?\n   - Can you share a particularly challenging decision you've had to make recently?\n\n5. **Personal Experience**\n   - What has been the most rewarding experience in your career so far?\n   - Who have been your biggest influences or mentors, and how have they shaped your approach to leadership?\n\n6. **Innovation and R&D**\n   - How does the company encourage innovation and creativity among employees?\n   - What exciting projects or developments are currently underway?\n\n7. **Employee Engagement**\n   - What initiatives does the company have in place to promote employee engagement and satisfaction?\n   - How can employees at all levels contribute to the company's success?\n\n8. **Corporate Responsibility**\n   - How does the company approach corporate social responsibility and sustainability?\n   - What recent CSR initiatives are you particularly proud of?\n\n9. **Risk Management**\n   - What are the biggest risks the company faces, and how are they being managed?\n   - How do you balance taking risks with maintaining stability?\n\n10. **Advice and Insights**\n    - What advice would you give someone looking to progress in their career within this industry?\n    - What do you wish you had known when you were starting your career?\n\nRemember, the conversation should be two-way, so be prepared to share your own thoughts and experiences as well. Showing that you have done your homework and understanding the context of the discussion will resonate well with the CEO.",
